The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 March is 40,415 (4,677.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 February, there were 518 new confirmed cases (60.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 February, there were 742 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (224 fewer cases).
